H0.text: In which county is Highgrove House the residence of the Prince of Wales. Cornwall

H1.text: In which county is Highgrove House the residence of the Prince of Wales. Norfolk

H2.text: In which county is Highgrove House the residence of the Prince of Wales. Surrey

H3.text: In which county is Highgrove House the residence of the Prince of Wales. Glos.

A4.text: Highgrove House is in Doughton in the civil parish of Tetbury Upton, near Tetbury in the county of Gloucestershire in South West England.

A5.text: It lies southwest of Tetbury in Gloucestershire, England.

A6.text: There are several royal residences in Gloucestershire, including Highgrove House, Gatcombe Park, and (formerly) Nether Lypiatt Manor.
